edu.wpi.grip.core.operations.networktables

Class NTPublishOperation<S,T extends NTPublishable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wpi.grip.core.operations.networktables.NTPublishOperation<S,T>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Operation

    public class NTPublishOperation<S,T extends NTPublishable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Operation
    An operation that publishes any type that implements NTPublishable to NetworkTables.

    To be publishable, a type should have one or more accessor methods annotated with NTValue. This is done with annotations instead of methods

      • NTPublishOperation

        public NTPublishOperation(java.lang.Class<S> socketType,
                          java.lang.Class<T> reportType,
                          java.util.function.Function<S,T> converter)
        Create a new publish operation where the socket type and NTPublishable type are different. This is useful for classes that we don't create, such as JavaCV's opencv_core.Size class, since we can't make them implement additional interfaces.
        Parameters:
        socketType - The type of socket that can be connected to this step
        reportType - A class implementing NTPublishable that determines what data is sent to NetworkTables
        converter - A function to convert socket values into publishable values
